        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Nothing escapes your ears so long as they move even an inch. You gain tremorsense as a vague sense with a range of 30 feet. This means you can use your ears to determine if a creature is present, but you can't pinpoint their location. Creatures that haven't moved or don't make sounds (such as those under the effects of a silence spell) remain undetected to you.</p>"
